      • encoderDrive

        public void encoderDrive(double driveFB,
                         double turnDegrees,
                         double speed,
                         boolean turning,
                         boolean timerRequested,
                         int timerRequestTime)
        **Not used directly by autonomous programs**

        See forward(double, double), backward(double, double), left(double, double), and right(double, double)

        Allows robot to be programmed to go forward, backward a certain amount of inches

        Allows robot to be programmed to turn left and right a certain number of degrees

        Parameters:
        driveFB - Inches to move forward or backward (forward: +, backward: -)
        turnDegrees - Degrees to turn left or right (right: +, left: -)
        speed - Speed of robot (min: 0, max: 1)
        turning - Whether the robot is currently turning
        timerRequested - Whether this move is timed
        timerRequestTime - If move is timed, length of move is milliseconds

        @Deprecated
public void encoderDriveBasic(double leftFrontInches,
                                           double rightFrontInches,
                                           double leftBackInches,
                                           double rightBackInches,
                                           double speed)
        Deprecated. 
        **Not Used Anymore**

        Replace by encoderDrive(double, double, double, boolean, boolean, int)

        Allows each individual motor to be programmed to go forward (+), backward (-) a certain amount of inches

        Parameters:
        leftFrontInches - Inches to move motorLeftFront
        rightFrontInches - Inches to move motorRightFront
        leftBackInches - Inches to move motorLeftBack
        rightBackInches - Inches to move motorRightBack
        speed - Speed of robot (min: 0, max: 1)

      • moveWinch

        public void moveWinch(double power,
                      long time)

        This is a simple function that controls the movement of the winch motor.

        Parameters:
        power - This is the power given to the winch motor. Negative power means that the winch will retract, lifting the robot. Positive power means that the winch will lower, lowering the robot.
        time - This is the time, in milliseconds, that the motor needs to spin.

      • vuforiaNavigation

        public void vuforiaNavigation(int camera_forward_displacement,
                              int camera_vertical_displacement,
                              int camera_left_displacement)
        Vuforia Navigation **Experimental, Not Tested, not for webcam

        This contains some of the Vuforia initialization code. The function also calculates the location of the robot based on the the VuMarks detected.

        Parameters:
        camera_forward_displacement - This is the forward location of the phone relative to the center of the robot.
        camera_vertical_displacement - This is the vertical location of the phone relative to the center of the robot.
        camera_left_displacement - This is the left location of the phone relative to the center of the robot.
